review_blob: 750ml bottle from the brewery. Pours a cloudy orange/dark amber. Big off-white head good retention. Pithy, citrus nose. Huge bitter hops, grapefruit & orange peel. Quite a thick mouth feel due to unfiltered nature. Nearest taste to this of a popular brew IMO is Sierra nevada torpedo. Draught @ Brewdog Liverpool. Pours jet black, tan head. Aroma ; dark fruit, liquorice & toffee. Thick oily texture. Tastes as aroma, plus Milk chocolate, sweet lactose. Abv quite well hidden. Very drinkable.
beer_name: To l Spildt Mlk (Boys Dont Cry Over Spilled Milk)

review_blob: Dark fruit, acidity, very low carbonation. Lots of red wine on the palette. Fairly boozy.

Draught @ Brewdog Liverpool. 330ml. Amber wheat beer, foamy head, cloudy. Aroma; banana, spice & citrus fruit. Taste; spicy, grapefruit, lemon. Reminds of a Belgian saison. Quite strong carbonation. Decent beer, refreshing.
Very dark, hazy brown. Thin head and sticky lacing. Aroma- liquorice, dandelion & burdock, sweetness. Taste reflects aroma. Thinner mouthfeel than expected and hides abv well. Classy brew.

Bottle from Brewdog online. Pours very dark red, almost black. Small tan head. Vanilla, spice & dark fruit aroma. Thick oily feel. Alcohol, chocolate, woody bourbon vanilla flavours. Excellent but prefer Paradox Arran.

355ml can from Jd Wetherspoons. Pours hazy orange amber, big, lasting head. Weak pine aroma. Good malty base balanced with big citrus hop. Quite thick mouth feel, but hides alcohol well. Very drinkable.
Strong Xmas ale. Plenty of hops and candy malt, liquorice and dark berries. Thickish mouth feel but cleanish finish.
Beautiful creamy foam, very warm and complex body of flavours. Alcohol 11%. Apparently based on piraat 10.5. My favorite beer on draught in Brugge.
